      "author_association": "OWNER",
      "body": "# feat: persist and list todos\n\nImplement the first slice of the todo CLI.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `TODO_DB=/path todo add \"Buy milk\"` persists a todo and prints `added 1`.\n- Titles are trimmed; an empty or whitespace-only title exits non-zero, prints\n  `title must not be empty` to stderr, and does not modify the database.\n- IDs start at 1 and increase monotonically.\n- `TODO_DB=/path todo list` prints one line per todo in ID order using exactly\n  `<id>\\t<status>\\t<title>`; new todos have status `active`.\n- State survives separate process invocations.\n- Add behavior-level tests. Use only the Go standard library.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `gofmt -w .`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n",
